%p#mission-statement
  The founding purpose of Ruby Australia is to further the use and adoption of
  the Ruby programming language in Australia, and to support and encourage a
  vibrant community around the language and related technologies.
  
%section#meetups
  %h3 Meetups
  %p
    There are a number of regional Ruby-related meetups all over the country.
    Each group is organised independently by its members, and all are very
    welcoming to newcomers. The following groups meet regularly:

  %ul.meetup-locations
    %li
      %a#roro-adl{href: '/meetups/roro-adl.html'} RoRo Adelaide
    %li
      %a#roro-bne{href: '/meetups/roro-bne.html'} RoRo Brisbane
    %li
      %a#roro-can{href: '/meetups/roro-can.html'} RoRo Canberra
    %li
      %a#roro-mel{href: '/meetups/roro-mel.html'} RoRo Melbourne
    %li
      %a#roro-per{href: '/meetups/roro-per.html'} RoRo Perth
    %li
      %a#roro-syd{href: '/meetups/roro-syd.html'} RoRo Sydney

%section#railscamp
  %h3 Rails Camp
  %p
    Ruby Australia is the organising body of Australian "Rails Camp" events.
    Please see the official <a href="http://railscamps.com">Rails camp</a> site
    for more details.

%section
  %h3 Join Ruby Australia
  %p
    Joining Ruby Australia is free. <a href="/join-ruby-australia.html">Join!</a>
  
  %h3 Contributing to the site
  %p
